HEADWORD: Stereographical
<hw>Ste`re*o*graph"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>st⟦eacute⟧r⟦eacute⟧ographique</ets>.]</ety> <def>Made
or done according to the rules of stereography; delineated on a plane;
<as>as, a <ex>stereographic</ex> chart of the earth</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Stereographic projection</b></col> <fld>(Geom.)</fld>,
<cd>a method of representing the sphere in which the center of
projection is taken in the surface of the sphere, and the plane upon
which the projection is made is at right andles to the diameter passing
through the center of projection.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stereographically</ent>⟦br⟧
